  <div class="box">
    <h3>Data Visualization & Graph Layer</h3>
    <p>Charts were rendered via <code>@flourish/live-api</code>, with <code>DuckDB-WASM</code> doing in-browser analytical queries against large datasets — meaning significant data processing happened client-side without a server round trip. The design challenge was making Flourish visualizations feel native to the interface rather than embedded from outside: chart entry, labeling, and source linkage were treated as interface moments, not just data outputs.</p>
    <p>Tabular data was handled by AG Grid, carrying the heavy lifting for large, filterable datasets while staying visually consistent with the broader design system built on Radix UI primitives and Tailwind. Algolia powered search across the data catalog via <code>react-instantsearch</code>.</p>
  </div>

